  .container
    h1.text-center.fw-bold.display-2.my-4.py-4 SpriteSpin
    .w-50.mx-auto(style="min-width: 320px")
      p SpriteSpin is library for playing animations from image frames. It requires an array of images or a stiched sprite sheet and plays them frame by frame like a flip book. The aim of this plugin is to provide a 360 degree view of any kind of product.
      p The library is built with extensibility in mind and comes with a plugin system to customize its behavior.

    #spritespin-preview
    script(type='text/javascript' src='/release/spritespin.js')
    script(type='text/javascript').
      SpriteSpin.create({
        target: '#spritespin-preview',
        source: SpriteSpin.source('http://spritespin.ginie.eu/images/rad_zoom_{frame}.jpg', {
          frame: [1,34],
          digits: 3,
        }),
        sense: -1
      })

    h2 NPM
    p install with npm
  .mb-3.bg-dark: pre.container: code.language-shell
    | $ npm install spritespin
  .container
